returns.playerisSleeping: If the player is sleeping or not
returns.playerdimension: The player's dimension (-1 in the Nether, 0 in the overworld)
returns.playerdeathTime: The amount of time of the remaining player should act 'dead'
returns.varsget: The variable's value that was set

methodDescriptions.consolesyslog: Logs a message to the system console with default Java logging
methodDescriptions.consolelog: Logs a message to the system console (with logger)
methodDescriptions.consolewarn: Logs a message as warning to the system console (with logger)
methodDescriptions.consoleerror: Logs a message as an issue to the system console (with logger)
methodDescriptions.playerinvdropAllItems: Drops all items as the player
methodDescriptions.playersend: Sends a message as the player
methodDescriptions.playerposition: Moves the player position, note that this isn't teleportation, since you can't clip through blocks
methodDescriptions.clientsetSplash: Allows you to replace the default splash with the provided string.
methodDescriptions.fontaddText: Adds text to the in-game screen
methodDescriptions.fontremoveText: Removes text from the in-game screen
